{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013q9pR6f7PpTfgZs5s7Eiho","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 17.1: Worktree Manager\n2\t\n3\tStatus: done\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want a worktree manager that handles git worktree create/merge/cleanup,\n9\tso that parallel epics run in isolated working directories.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` exists, **when** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **then** it creates a git branch named `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug}` from the current HEAD of the main branch. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n14\t\n15\t2. **Given** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **when** the branch is created, **then** it creates a git worktree at `/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{epicId}` pointing to the new branch and returns the absolute worktree path. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t3. **Given** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **when** the operation completes, **then** the total wall-clock time is under 10 seconds (NFR1). <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t4. **Given** `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` is called, **when** a worktree exists for that epicId, **then** the worktree is removed via `git worktree remove` and the branch `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-*` is deleted via `git branch -D`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t5. **Given** `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` is called, **when** no worktree exists for that epicId, **then** the function completes without error (idempotent). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t6. **Given** `listWorktrees()` is called, **when** one or more codeharness worktrees exist, **then** it returns an array of `WorktreeInfo` objects containing `epicId`, `path`, `branch`, and `createdAt` for every worktree whose branch starts with `codeharness/epic-`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t7. **Given** `listWorktrees()` is called, **when** no codeharness worktrees exist, **then** it returns an empty array. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t8. **Given** orphaned worktrees from a previous crashed run exist (worktree directory present but no active codeharness process), **when** `detectOrphans()` is called, **then** it returns an array of orphaned `WorktreeInfo` entries whose worktree paths are present on disk but not tracked by any running codeharness process. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t9. **Given** `createWorktree` is called, **when** the branch `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug}` already exists (stale from a crash), **then** the function cleans up the stale branch and worktree before re-creating, rather than throwing. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t10. **Given** `createWorktree` is called, **when** the git command fails (e.g., not a git repo, disk full), **then** a descriptive `WorktreeError` is thrown with the stderr from the git command, and any partially-created branch or worktree is cleaned up. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t11. **Given** all git operations in worktree-manager, **when** they execute, **then** stderr is captured and included in error messages, and branch names are prefixed with `codeharness/` to avoid collision with user branches (NFR12). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n36\t\n37\t- [x] Task 1: Create `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` with types and interfaces (AC: #1, #2, #6, #8, #11)\n38\t  - [x] Define `WorktreeInfo` interface: `epicId`, `path`, `branch`, `createdAt`\n39\t  - [x] Define `WorktreeError` error class extending `Error` with `stderr` field\n40\t  - [x] Define `WorktreeManager` class with constructor accepting `mainBranch: string` (default `'main'`)\n41\t  - [x] Constants: `BRANCH_PREFIX = 'codeharness/epic-'`, `WORKTREE_BASE = '/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-'`\n42\t\n43\t- [x] Task 2: Implement `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #9, #10)\n44\t  - [x] Run `git branch codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug} {mainBranch}` via `execSync`\n45\t  - [x] Run `git worktree add /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{epicId} codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug}` via `execSync`\n46\t  - [x] On branch-already-exists: call cleanup first, then retry create (AC #9)\n47\t  - [x] On any failure: clean up partial state (remove worktree if created, delete branch if created)\n48\t  - [x] Wrap git stderr in `WorktreeError`\n49\t  - [x] Return absolute worktree path\n50\t\n51\t- [x] Task 3: Implement `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` (AC: #4, #5)\n52\t  - [x] Find the branch matching `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-*` via `git branch --list`\n53\t  - [x] Run `git worktree remove /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{epicId} --force`\n54\t  - [x] Run `git branch -D {branch}` to delete the branch\n55\t  - [x] Swallow errors if worktree or branch doesn't exist (idempotent, AC #5)\n56\t\n57\t- [x] Task 4: Implement `listWorktrees()` (AC: #6, #7)\n58\t  - [x] Run `git worktree list --porcelain` and parse output\n59\t  - [x] Filter to entries whose branch starts with `codeharness/epic-`\n60\t  - [x] Extract epicId from branch name pattern `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug}`\n61\t  - [x] Return `WorktreeInfo[]` sorted by epicId\n62\t\n63\t- [x] Task 5: Implement `detectOrphans()` (AC: #8)\n64\t  - [x] Call `listWorktrees()` to get all codeharness worktrees\n65\t  - [x] Check each worktree path for a `.codeharness/lane-state.json` file\n66\t  - [x] If lane-state.json doesn't exist or has no active PID, mark as orphan\n67\t  - [x] Return orphaned `WorktreeInfo[]`\n68\t\n69\t- [x] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#11)\n70\t  - [x] Test: createWorktree creates branch and worktree, returns path\n71\t  - [x] Test: createWorktree cleans up stale branch before re-creating\n72\t  - [x] Test: createWorktree throws WorktreeError with stderr on git failure\n73\t  - [x] Test: createWorktree cleans up partial state on failure\n74\t  - [x] Test: cleanupWorktree removes worktree and branch\n75\t  - [x] Test: cleanupWorktree is idempotent (no error when nothing exists)\n76\t  - [x] Test: listWorktrees returns only codeharness-prefixed worktrees\n77\t  - [x] Test: listWorktrees returns empty array when none exist\n78\t  - [x] Test: detectOrphans identifies worktrees without active process\n79\t  - [x] Test: branch names use codeharness/ prefix (NFR12)\n80\t  - [x] Test: all error messages include stderr from git\n81\t\n82\t## Dev Notes\n83\t\n84\t### Architecture Constraints\n85\t\n86\t- **Architecture Decision 1** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): Each parallel epic gets its own git worktree on a dedicated branch. The worktree manager handles the full lifecycle: create -> execute -> merge -> validate -> cleanup. This story covers create, cleanup, list, and orphan detection. Merge is deferred to Story 18-1.\n87\t- **Worktree Operations Pattern**: All git operations MUST use `child_process.execSync` for atomic git commands (create branch, add worktree). Use `child_process.exec` with timeout for potentially slow operations. Capture stderr for error reporting. Clean up on failure.\n88\t- **Branch naming**: `codeharness/` prefix prevents collision with user branches (NFR12).\n89\t- **Worktree location**: `/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{N}` -- temporary, cleaned up after merge.\n90\t\n91\t### Key Files to Create\n92\t\n93\t| File | Purpose |\n94\t|------|---------|\n95\t| `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` | Git worktree lifecycle module |\n96\t| `src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` | Unit tests |\n97\t\n98\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n99\t\n100\t| File | Why |\n101\t|------|-----|\n102\t| `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` | `ExecutionConfig` interface -- has `isolation: 'worktree' \\| 'none'`. Worktree manager is used when `isolation === 'worktree'`. |\n103\t| `src/lib/null-task-registry.ts` | Pattern reference for registry modules with interfaces + error class. Follow the same module structure. |\n104\t| `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts` | Pattern reference for `appendFileSync`/`mkdirSync` file operations, `node:fs` imports, test patterns. |\n105\t| `src/lib/session-manager.ts` | Pattern reference for `child_process` usage in this codebase. |\n106\t\n107\t### Implementation Patterns\n108\t\n109\t**Git command execution:**\n110\t```typescript\n111\timport { execSync } from 'node:child_process';\n112\t\n113\t// Atomic git commands — use execSync\n114\texecSync(`git branch ${branchName} ${mainBranch}`, {\n115\t  cwd: projectDir,\n116\t  stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],  // capture stderr\n117\t});\n118\t\n119\t// Parse git worktree list --porcelain output:\n120\t// worktree /path/to/worktree\n121\t// HEAD abc123\n122\t// branch refs/heads/codeharness/epic-17-worktree-manager\n123\t// (blank line)\n124\t```\n125\t\n126\t**Error handling:**\n127\t```typescript\n128\ttry {\n129\t  execSync(cmd, { cwd, stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'] });\n130\t} catch (err: unknown) {\n131\t  const stderr = (err as { stderr?: Buffer })?.stderr?.toString() ?? '';\n132\t  throw new WorktreeError(`Failed to create worktree: ${stderr}`, stderr);\n133\t}\n134\t```\n135\t\n136\t**Testing strategy:** Mock `execSync` with `vi.mock('node:child_process')`. Verify correct git commands are called with correct arguments. Test error paths by making mock throw with stderr buffer.\n137\t\n138\t### Previous Story (16-6) Intelligence\n139\t\n140\t- Story 16-6 completed the story flow execution. All 4779 tests pass. This is the first story in Epic 17 -- a new module with no modifications to existing files.\n141\t- Recent code patterns: TypeScript modules in `src/lib/`, tests colocated in `__tests__/`, ESM with `.js` import extensions, vitest test framework.\n142\t- Module pattern: export interfaces, export functions or class, export error class. JSDoc comments on all exports.\n143\t- The workflow engine already has `ExecutionConfig` parsed from YAML. The worktree manager will be consumed by the lane pool (Story 17-2) and the merge serialization (Story 18-1).\n144\t\n145\t### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n146\t\n147\t- **Merge operations** -- deferred to Story 18-1. This story has no `mergeWorktree()` method.\n148\t- **Lane pool integration** -- deferred to Story 17-2. The worktree manager is a standalone module.\n149\t- **Run command integration** -- deferred to Story 17-3.\n150\t- **TUI components** -- deferred to Epic 20.\n151\t\n152\t### Edge Cases\n153\t\n154\t- **Stale branch from crash**: If `codeharness/epic-17-slug` already exists when `createWorktree` is called, the previous run crashed. Clean up the stale state before re-creating (AC #9). Do not throw.\n155\t- **Worktree directory already exists on disk**: `/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-17` might exist from a crash. `git worktree add` will fail. Handle by removing the directory first.\n156\t- **Not a git repo**: `execSync` throws. Wrap in `WorktreeError` with descriptive message.\n157\t- **Branch name with special characters**: The `slug` parameter comes from epic names. Sanitize to `[a-z0-9-]` before using in branch name.\n158\t- **Concurrent createWorktree calls**: Two calls with different epicIds are safe (different branches, different paths). Two calls with the same epicId are a bug in the caller -- the second will hit the stale-cleanup path.\n159\t\n160\t### Project Structure Notes\n161\t\n162\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n163\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/` directories\n164\t- ESM modules -- use `.js` extensions in imports\n165\t- Build: `npm run build`\n166\t- Test: `npm test`\n167\t\n168\t### References\n169\t\n170\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 17.1]\n171\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 1 — Worktree Lifecycle Model]\n172\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Worktree Operations Pattern]\n173\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Architectural Boundaries — Worktree Manager]\n174\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#FR6, FR7, FR11]\n175\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#NFR1, NFR9, NFR12]\n176\t\n177\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n178\t## Verification Requirements\n179\t\n180\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/17-1-worktree-manager-proof.md)\n181\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n182\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n183\t\n184\t## Documentation Requirements\n185\t\n186\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n187\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/17-1-worktree-manager.md\n188\t\n189\t## Testing Requirements\n190\t\n191\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n192\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n193\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n194\t\n195\t## Dev Agent Record\n196\t\n197\t### Agent Model Used\n198\t\n199\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n200\t\n201\t### Debug Log References\n202\t\n203\tNone.\n204\t\n205\t### Completion Notes List\n206\t\n207\t- Implemented `WorktreeManager` class with `createWorktree`, `cleanupWorktree`, `listWorktrees`, and `detectOrphans` methods\n208\t- All git operations use `execSync` with stdio piped for stderr capture\n209\t- Slug sanitization enforces `[a-z0-9-]` pattern\n210\t- Stale state from crashed runs is cleaned up before re-creating (AC #9)\n211\t- Partial state is cleaned up on failure (AC #10)\n212\t- All catch blocks annotated with `// IGNORE:` comments per NFR3 boundary enforcement\n213\t- 33 unit tests covering all 11 acceptance criteria\n214\t- Full regression suite passes: 4813 tests across 178 files\n215\t- Code review fixes applied: epicId validation (command injection prevention), createdAt uses filesystem birthtime instead of current time, dead code path removed, branch coverage gaps closed\n216\t\n217\t### Change Log\n218\t\n219\t- 2026-04-03: Implemented story 17-1 — worktree manager module with full test coverage\n220\t- 2026-04-03: Code review — fixed command injection via epicId validation, fixed createdAt to use fs birthtime, removed dead code path, added 8 tests for coverage gaps\n221\t\n222\t### File List\n223\t\n224\t- `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` (new) — WorktreeManager class, WorktreeInfo interface, WorktreeError class\n225\t- `src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` (new) — 25 unit tests covering all ACs\n226\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VgpeTZfnrFArETEmV1Y2uT","session_id":"1e0d780f-040f-4c10-b8e5-df49ae6fae2c","uuid":"8754b257-6d51-4e35-a022-26a5209fc568","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:40:05.957Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CzAvjnwRUKbsZfgiswiVJR","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 17.2: Lane Pool\n2\t\n3\tStatus: done\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want a lane pool that schedules epics concurrently up to `max_parallel`,\n9\tso that the engine runs multiple epics simultaneously.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` exists, **when** `startPool(epics, maxParallel)` is called, **then** it creates up to `maxParallel` lanes simultaneously, each backed by a worktree created via `WorktreeManager.createWorktree()`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n14\t\n15\t2. **Given** `startPool(epics, maxParallel)` is called with `maxParallel: 2` and 4 epics, **when** two lanes are active, **then** only 2 worktrees exist concurrently and the remaining epics wait in the pending queue. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t3. **Given** each lane is created, **when** the lane starts executing, **then** it runs the workflow engine (via a provided `executeEpic` callback) for that epic's stories using the worktree path as `cwd`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t4. **Given** multiple lanes are active, **when** any lane completes (its `Promise` resolves), **then** `Promise.race` detects the completion and the next independent epic is scheduled into the freed lane. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t5. **Given** the pending epic queue, **when** selecting the next epic to schedule, **then** epic independence is determined by epic ordering — epic N is ready only if no epic with index < N is still active (except those already done). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t6. **Given** lane lifecycle events occur (lane started, lane completed, lane failed), **when** the pool is running, **then** the pool emits `LaneEvent` objects consumable by the caller (for TUI consumption). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t7. **Given** `maxParallel: 1` in the execution config, **when** `startPool` runs, **then** epics execute sequentially one at a time — identical behavior to the current single-epic execution model (NFR10 backward compat). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t8. **Given** a lane's workflow engine promise rejects (epic execution crashes), **when** the error is caught, **then** the pool marks that lane as failed, cleans up its worktree via `WorktreeManager.cleanupWorktree()`, emits a `lane-failed` event, and continues scheduling remaining epics (NFR6 crash isolation). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t9. **Given** `startPool` is called, **when** all epics have been processed (completed or failed), **then** the pool resolves with a `PoolResult` containing per-epic results (success/failure, duration, errors). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t10. **Given** `LaneEvent` objects, **when** emitted by the pool, **then** each event includes `type` (`lane-started` | `lane-completed` | `lane-failed` | `epic-queued`), `epicId`, `laneIndex`, and a timestamp. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t11. **Given** `startPool` is called with an empty epics array, **when** the pool runs, **then** it resolves immediately with a `PoolResult` containing zero epics processed and `success: true`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t12. **Given** all exports from `lane-pool.ts`, **when** inspected, **then** `LanePool`, `LaneEvent`, `PoolResult`, `LaneStatus`, and `EpicDescriptor` types are exported and documented with JSDoc. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n36\t\n37\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n38\t\n39\t- [x] Task 1: Create `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` with types and interfaces (AC: #1, #6, #10, #12)\n40\t  - [x] Define `EpicDescriptor` interface: `id: string`, `slug: string`, `stories: string[]`\n41\t  - [x] Define `LaneStatus` type: `'executing' | 'completed' | 'failed'`\n42\t  - [x] Define `Lane` interface: `epicId: string`, `laneIndex: number`, `worktreePath: string`, `status: LaneStatus`, `promise: Promise<EngineResult>`\n43\t  - [x] Define `LaneEvent` interface: `type: 'lane-started' | 'lane-completed' | 'lane-failed' | 'epic-queued'`, `epicId: string`, `laneIndex: number`, `timestamp: string`, `error?: string`, `result?: EngineResult`\n44\t  - [x] Define `PoolResult` interface: `success: boolean`, `epicsProcessed: number`, `epicResults: Map<string, EpicResult>`, `durationMs: number`\n45\t  - [x] Define `EpicResult` interface: `epicId: string`, `status: 'completed' | 'failed'`, `engineResult?: EngineResult`, `error?: string`, `durationMs: number`\n46\t  - [x] Define `ExecuteEpicFn` callback type: `(epicId: string, worktreePath: string) => Promise<EngineResult>`\n47\t  - [x] JSDoc all exports\n48\t\n49\t- [x] Task 2: Implement `LanePool` class constructor and lane scheduling (AC: #1, #2, #5, #7)\n50\t  - [x] Constructor accepts `worktreeManager: WorktreeManager`, `maxParallel: number`\n51\t  - [x] `startPool(epics: EpicDescriptor[], executeFn: ExecuteEpicFn)` method\n52\t  - [x] Internal state: `activeLanes: Map<string, Lane>`, `pendingEpics: EpicDescriptor[]`, `completedEpicIds: Set<string>`\n53\t  - [x] Fill lanes up to `maxParallel` from the head of the pending queue\n54\t  - [x] Dependency check: `isEpicReady(epicIndex)` — true only if no epic with lower index is active (not in `completedEpicIds` and not failed)\n55\t\n56\t- [x] Task 3: Implement the `Promise.race` scheduling loop (AC: #3, #4, #8, #9)\n57\t  - [x] Create a `createLane(epic)` method: calls `worktreeManager.createWorktree(epic.id, epic.slug)`, then calls `executeFn(epic.id, worktreePath)`\n58\t  - [x] Main loop: `while (pendingEpics.length > 0 || activeLanes.size > 0)` → fill lanes → `Promise.race` on active → process completion\n59\t  - [x] On lane success: add to `completedEpicIds`, record `EpicResult`, emit `lane-completed` event\n60\t  - [x] On lane failure: add to failed set, call `worktreeManager.cleanupWorktree(epicId)`, record `EpicResult` with error, emit `lane-failed` event\n61\t  - [x] After loop: return `PoolResult`\n62\t\n63\t- [x] Task 4: Implement event emission (AC: #6, #10)\n64\t  - [x] Internal `EventEmitter` or callback array for `LaneEvent` delivery\n65\t  - [x] `onEvent(callback: (event: LaneEvent) => void)` method for registering listeners\n66\t  - [x] Emit `lane-started` when a lane is created\n67\t  - [x] Emit `lane-completed` when a lane's promise resolves\n68\t  - [x] Emit `lane-failed` when a lane's promise rejects\n69\t  - [x] Emit `epic-queued` when an epic enters the pending queue\n70\t  - [x] All events include ISO 8601 timestamp\n71\t\n72\t- [x] Task 5: Handle edge cases (AC: #8, #11)\n73\t  - [x] Empty epics array: return immediately with empty `PoolResult`\n74\t  - [x] Worktree creation failure: treat as lane failure (don't crash the pool)\n75\t  - [x] All epics fail: pool still resolves (not rejects) with `success: false`\n76\t  - [x] Cleanup on pool completion: ensure no dangling promises\n77\t\n78\t- [x] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#12)\n79\t  - [x] Test: startPool creates up to maxParallel lanes simultaneously\n80\t  - [x] Test: startPool with maxParallel=2 and 4 epics — only 2 active at a time\n81\t  - [x] Test: each lane receives correct worktree path from WorktreeManager\n82\t  - [x] Test: Promise.race picks up completion and schedules next epic\n83\t  - [x] Test: epic independence — epic N waits for epic N-1 unless N-1 is done\n84\t  - [x] Test: LaneEvent objects are emitted with correct types and fields\n85\t  - [x] Test: maxParallel=1 executes epics sequentially\n86\t  - [x] Test: lane failure cleans up worktree and continues\n87\t  - [x] Test: pool result contains per-epic results\n88\t  - [x] Test: empty epics array returns success immediately\n89\t  - [x] Test: all types are exported from lane-pool.ts\n90\t  - [x] Test: worktree creation failure treated as lane failure (pool continues)\n91\t\n92\t## Dev Notes\n93\t\n94\t### Architecture Constraints\n95\t\n96\t- **Architecture Decision 2** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): The engine maintains a fixed-size lane pool. Each lane is an async task (not a separate process) that runs a workflow engine instance against a worktree directory. `Promise.race()` on active lanes detects completion. When any lane completes, its result is processed and next epic scheduled.\n97\t- **Lane Pool Boundary** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): Manages lane lifecycle and scheduling. Does NOT execute stories directly. Delegates to workflow engine instances per lane. Interface: `startPool(epics, maxParallel) → PoolResult`.\n98\t- **Lane Isolation Pattern**: Each lane MUST set `cwd` to its worktree path for all agent dispatches. Lanes share no state during execution; results are collected at pool completion.\n99\t\n100\t### Key Files to Create\n101\t\n102\t| File | Purpose |\n103\t|------|---------|\n104\t| `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` | Lane pool scheduling module |\n105\t| `src/lib/__tests__/lane-pool.test.ts` | Unit tests |\n106\t\n107\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n108\t\n109\t| File | Why |\n110\t|------|-----|\n111\t| `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` | `WorktreeManager` class — used by the pool to create/cleanup worktrees. Understand the `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` and `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` APIs. |\n112\t| `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` | `ExecutionConfig` interface — has `max_parallel` and `epic_strategy`. Lane pool reads `max_parallel` from this config. |\n113\t| `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` | `EngineResult` interface — returned by the execute callback. Has `success`, `tasksCompleted`, `storiesProcessed`, `errors`, `durationMs`. |\n114\t| `src/lib/null-task-registry.ts` | Pattern reference for registry modules with interfaces + error class. Follow the same module structure. |\n115\t| `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts` | Pattern reference for module structure, JSDoc conventions, error handling. |\n116\t\n117\t### Implementation Patterns\n118\t\n119\t**Promise.race scheduling loop:**\n120\t```typescript\n121\twhile (pendingEpics.length > 0 || activeLanes.size > 0) {\n122\t  // Fill lanes up to max\n123\t  while (activeLanes.size < maxLanes && hasReadyEpic()) {\n124\t    const epic = nextReadyEpic();\n125\t    const lane = await createLane(epic);\n126\t    activeLanes.set(epic.id, lane);\n127\t  }\n128\t  // Wait for any lane to complete\n129\t  if (activeLanes.size === 0) break;\n130\t  const completed = await Promise.race(\n131\t    [...activeLanes.values()].map(l =>\n132\t      l.promise.then(\n133\t        result => ({ epicId: l.epicId, result, error: undefined }),\n134\t        error => ({ epicId: l.epicId, result: undefined, error }),\n135\t      )\n136\t    )\n137\t  );\n138\t  // Process completion: record result, free lane, schedule next\n139\t  await processLaneCompletion(completed);\n140\t}\n141\t```\n142\t\n143\t**Lane event emission:**\n144\t```typescript\n145\tprivate emit(event: LaneEvent): void {\n146\t  for (const listener of this.listeners) {\n147\t    listener(event);\n148\t  }\n149\t}\n150\t```\n151\t\n152\t**Epic independence check:**\n153\t```typescript\n154\tprivate isEpicReady(epicIndex: number): boolean {\n155\t  // Epic N is ready only if no epic with index < N is still active\n156\t  for (const [, lane] of this.activeLanes) {\n157\t    const activeIndex = this.epicIndexMap.get(lane.epicId);\n158\t    if (activeIndex !== undefined && activeIndex < epicIndex) {\n159\t      return false;\n160\t    }\n161\t  }\n162\t  return true;\n163\t}\n164\t```\n165\t\n166\t**Testing strategy:** Mock `WorktreeManager` with `vi.fn()` stubs. Provide a fake `executeFn` callback that resolves/rejects to simulate engine execution. Use `vi.useFakeTimers()` if timestamp assertions are needed. Verify event emission order with a captured event array.\n167\t\n168\t### Previous Story (17-1) Intelligence\n169\t\n170\t- Story 17-1 completed the worktree manager module. All 4813 tests pass across 178 files. The worktree manager provides `createWorktree(epicId, slug) → string` (returns worktree path) and `cleanupWorktree(epicId) → void`.\n171\t- Module patterns: TypeScript in `src/lib/`, tests in `src/lib/__tests__/`, ESM with `.js` import extensions, vitest test framework.\n172\t- Constructor pattern: `WorktreeManager` accepts `mainBranch` and optional `cwd`. Lane pool should accept `WorktreeManager` instance (dependency injection).\n173\t- Error pattern: `WorktreeError` extends `Error` with `stderr` field. Lane pool should define `LanePoolError` if needed.\n174\t\n175\t### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n176\t\n177\t- **Run command integration** — deferred to Story 17-3. The lane pool is a standalone module.\n178\t- **Merge operations** — deferred to Epic 18. The pool creates/cleans up worktrees but does not merge.\n179\t- **TUI components** — deferred to Epic 20. The pool emits `LaneEvent` objects but does not render them.\n180\t- **Epic completion detection** — deferred to Story 19-1. The pool just schedules and tracks lane completion.\n181\t- **State file management** — the pool does not read or write sprint-state.json. The `executeFn` callback handles that internally.\n182\t\n183\t### Edge Cases\n184\t\n185\t- **Empty epics array**: Return immediately with empty `PoolResult` (AC #11).\n186\t- **All epics fail**: Pool resolves (not rejects) with `success: false`. Each failed epic has its worktree cleaned up.\n187\t- **Worktree creation failure**: `WorktreeManager.createWorktree()` throws `WorktreeError`. The pool should catch this, treat it as a lane failure, and continue with remaining epics.\n188\t- **executeFn rejects with non-Error**: Wrap in a descriptive error string for the `EpicResult`.\n189\t- **maxParallel > number of epics**: Pool creates one lane per epic (never more lanes than epics).\n190\t- **Single epic with maxParallel > 1**: One lane, completes, pool finishes.\n191\t- **Concurrent Promise.race identity**: When wrapping promises in `.then()` for `Promise.race`, each wrapper must include the `epicId` so the pool knows which lane completed.\n192\t\n193\t### Project Structure Notes\n194\t\n195\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n196\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/` directories\n197\t- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n198\t- Build: `npm run build`\n199\t- Test: `npm test`\n200\t\n201\t### References\n202\t\n203\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 17.2]\n204\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 2 — Lane Pool & Scheduling]\n205\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Lane Pool Boundary]\n206\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Lane Isolation Pattern]\n207\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#FR9, FR10]\n208\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#NFR6, NFR10]\n209\t\n210\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n211\t## Verification Requirements\n212\t\n213\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/17-2-lane-pool-proof.md)\n214\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n215\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n216\t\n217\t## Documentation Requirements\n218\t\n219\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n220\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/17-2-lane-pool.md\n221\t\n222\t## Testing Requirements\n223\t\n224\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n225\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n226\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n227\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VgpeTZfnrFArETEmV1Y2uT","session_id":"1e0d780f-040f-4c10-b8e5-df49ae6fae2c","uuid":"c63dd4ea-de0c-4afb-8fe7-9ee79b4b0572","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:40:05.988Z"}
