ns: 3 similar glob patterns for story files\n\n### 17-2-lane-pool — dev-story (2026-04-04T20:16)\n\n- Epic independence semantics (AC #5): batch-style parallelism, not sliding-window. Epic 3 won't start until ALL preceding epics complete, even if epic 1 finishes while epic 2 is still running. Matches spec but may surprise users.\n- No workarounds or TODOs.\n- Empty catch blocks annotated with `// IGNORE:` per project lint rules.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 20\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 4, Grep: 3, Write: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~30 lines), first test run failure (~45 lines), `npx vitest run` (~15 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 17-2-lane-pool — code-review (2026-04-04T20:22)\n\n- 0 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM (all coverage gaps — fixed), 3 LOW (unreachable defensive code)\n- Coverage after fixes: 100% statements, 91.17% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines\n- LOW: Unreachable `?? 'Unknown error'` fallback and `activeIndex !== undefined` guard — defensive but unnecessary\n- LOW: No test for pool reuse (calling startPool twice)\n- Architecture note: candidate batching bypasses independence check for initial batch — fine for small maxParallel but could over-schedule with large values\n- createWorktree uses execSync, blocking event loop — inherited from WorktreeManager design\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~50 lines), verbose test run (~40 lines), coverage run 2 (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 17-2-lane-pool — verification (2026-04-04T20:31)\n\n- **`codeharness verify` precondition failure**: AGENTS.md for `src/lib` did not reference `lane-pool.ts`. Fixed by adding entry to AGENTS.md.\n- **BATS test warnings**: `npm test` output polluted with BW01 warnings from BATS integration tests. Pre-existing.\n- **Branch coverage 91.17%**: Uncovered branches at lines 291-306, 398 (defensive fallbacks). Stmts/funcs/lines all 100%.\n- **Verification gap**: AC5 (epic independence) verified by single test with 3 epics.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 3, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run --coverage` (~80 lines), `npm test` (~60 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: npm test ran twice, coverage command ran twice\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":42,"oldLines":6,"newStart":42,"newLines":22,"lines":[" - Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads"," - Redundant operations: none"," ","+### 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration — create-story (2026-04-04T20:42)","+","+- No ambiguities in epic definition.","+- Workaround: `--resume` + parallel mode edge case not covered — deferred to Epic 18/19.","+- Risk: executeFn agent resolution is shared across worktrees — fine while agents are stateless config objects.","+- Observation: Docker pre-flight check preserved in parallel path (harmless but unnecessary).","+","+## Token Report","+- Total tool calls: 16","+- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 7, Grep: 5, Write: 1, Glob: 5","+- Largest Bash outputs: `ls implementation-artifacts` (~230 lines)","+- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads","+- Redundant operations: None","+","+---","+"," ### 17-2-lane-pool — verification (2026-04-04T20:31)"," "," - **`codeharness verify` precondition failure**: AGENTS.md for `src/lib` did not reference `lane-pool.ts`. Fixed by adding entry to AGENTS.md."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
