{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YVAicDPB2Xe9r2bfCAtkWv","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 61 tests pass (40 existing + 21 new).\n\n---\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n\n### Modified files:\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts` -- Added parallel execution branch that detects `execution.epic_strategy === 'parallel'`, creates `WorktreeManager` + `LanePool`, discovers epics from sprint state, executes via the pool, logs lane events, reports results, and checks for remaining worktrees. Sequential path preserved unchanged. Added exported helpers `extractEpicId()` and `buildEpicDescriptors()`.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/17-3-run-command-parallel-integration.md` -- Status set to `review`, all tasks/subtasks marked done.\n\n### New files:\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/run-parallel.test.ts` -- 21 tests covering all 12 ACs: extractEpicId unit tests, buildEpicDescriptors unit tests, parallel mode detection, sequential backward compatibility, LanePool construction with correct maxParallel, executeFn projectDir propagation, exit code mapping, lane event logging, max_parallel=1 behavior, worktree isolation forcing, crash isolation, remaining worktree warnings, sprint state failure, no-pending-epics edge case, and error handling.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Vitest mock pattern**: `vi.fn()` mocks cannot be used with `new` via `mockReturnValue`. Had to create actual ES classes in the hoisted block that delegate to mutable factory functions. This pattern is non-obvious but works correctly -- a potential source of confusion for future maintainers.\n- **File length**: `run.ts` grew from 203 to 340 lines. The story notes mention an NFR9 of max 300 lines per file. The parallel path could be extracted to `run-parallel.ts` in a follow-up if enforcement is strict.\n- **No integration test with real LanePool/WorktreeManager**: All tests mock the pool and worktree manager. Real end-to-end behavior (git worktree creation, concurrent execution) is not tested at this level -- that would require integration tests with a real git repo.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 30\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 10, Edit: 18, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx tsc --noEmit` (~33 lines), `npx vitest run run-parallel.test.ts` first attempt (~40 lines), `npx vitest run` grep for failures (~22 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: None significant. Two vitest runs on the parallel test file were needed to diagnose the mock constructor issue, but those were debugging iterations, not wasted calls."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a658428d05d0c15f2 (use SendMessage with to: 'a658428d05d0c15f2' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 111506\ntool_uses: 66\nduration_ms: 695468</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e0d780f-040f-4c10-b8e5-df49ae6fae2c","uuid":"66c4e43e-17a5-464e-ba32-34630c544759","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:56:37.594Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/17-3-run-command-parallel-integration.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing 