{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014v6AyMyndQLAFRoRZaLFJm","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 17.3: Run Command Parallel Integration\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a user,\n8\tI want `codeharness run` to use the lane pool when `execution.epic_strategy: parallel`,\n9\tso that parallel execution works end-to-end.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** a workflow with `execution: { max_parallel: 2, epic_strategy: parallel }`, **when** `codeharness run` executes, **then** the run command reads the `execution` config from the resolved workflow's `ResolvedWorkflow.execution` field. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n14\t\n15\t2. **Given** `execution.epic_strategy` is `'parallel'` and `execution.max_parallel >= 2`, **when** the run command starts, **then** it creates a `LanePool` instance with the `WorktreeManager` and `max_parallel` from the execution config. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t3. **Given** the lane pool is created, **when** the run command builds the epic list, **then** it reads all pending epics from the sprint state (epics whose status is not `'done'`) and converts them to `EpicDescriptor[]` with `id`, `slug`, and `stories` fields populated from the sprint state's story keys. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t4. **Given** the lane pool is created with pending epics, **when** `startPool(epics, executeFn)` is called, **then** each epic's `executeFn` callback invokes `executeWorkflow` with `EngineConfig.projectDir` set to the worktree path provided by the lane pool. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t5. **Given** epics are executing in parallel via the lane pool, **when** stories within each epic run, **then** they execute sequentially within their worktree (the engine's existing sequential behavior is preserved per lane). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t6. **Given** a lane's workflow engine promise rejects (epic execution crashes), **when** the error is caught by the lane pool, **then** the crash does not affect other active lanes and the run command continues until all epics are processed (NFR6 crash isolation). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t7. **Given** all epics have been processed (completed or failed) by the lane pool, **when** the pool returns `PoolResult`, **then** the run command reports final results: total epics processed, per-epic success/failure, total stories processed, total duration, and exits with code 0 if all succeeded or code 1 if any failed. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t8. **Given** `execution.epic_strategy` is `'sequential'` (the default), **when** `codeharness run` executes, **then** the run command uses the existing single-engine execution path (no lane pool, no worktree manager) — backward compatible with the current behavior. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t9. **Given** `execution.epic_strategy` is `'parallel'` but `max_parallel` is `1`, **when** the run command starts, **then** it creates a lane pool with `maxParallel: 1`, producing sequential execution through the pool (one lane at a time) identical to sequential strategy (NFR10). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t10. **Given** the lane pool emits `LaneEvent` objects during execution, **when** the run command receives them, **then** it logs lane lifecycle events (lane started, lane completed, lane failed) to the console output using `info()`. <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t11. **Given** the run command in parallel mode, **when** it finishes execution, **then** all worktrees created during the run are cleaned up (via `WorktreeManager.cleanupWorktree` called by the lane pool on completion/failure). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t12. **Given** the resolved workflow has `execution.isolation` set to `'worktree'`, **when** `epic_strategy` is `'parallel'`, **then** the run command creates worktrees for each epic. **And given** `isolation` is `'none'` (the default), **when** `epic_strategy` is `'parallel'`, **then** the run command still uses worktree isolation (parallel requires worktrees regardless of the isolation field). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n36\t\n37\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n38\t\n39\t- [x] Task 1: Modify `src/commands/run.ts` to detect parallel execution config (AC: #1, #8, #12)\n40\t  - [x] After resolving the workflow, read `parsedWorkflow.execution.epic_strategy` and `parsedWorkflow.execution.max_parallel`\n41\t  - [x] If `epic_strategy === 'parallel'`, branch into parallel execution path\n42\t  - [x] If `epic_strategy === 'sequential'` (or default), preserve existing single-engine path unchanged (AC #8)\n43\t\n44\t- [x] Task 2: Implement epic discovery from sprint state (AC: #3)\n45\t  - [x] Read sprint state via `getSprintState()` from `src/modules/sprint/index.ts`\n46\t  - [x] Group stories by epic ID (extract epic prefix from story key, e.g., `17-1-foo` -> epic `17`)\n47\t  - [x] Filter to epics whose status is not `'done'` in `state.epics`\n48\t  - [x] Build `EpicDescriptor[]` with `id` (epic number), `slug` (sanitized epic name), `stories` (story keys belonging to that epic)\n49\t\n50\t- [x] Task 3: Implement parallel execution path in run command (AC: #2, #4, #5, #9, #12)\n51\t  - [x] Import `WorktreeManager` from `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts`\n52\t  - [x] Import `LanePool` from `src/lib/lane-pool.ts`\n53\t  - [x] Create `WorktreeManager` instance (default main branch)\n54\t  - [x] Create `LanePool` with `worktreeManager` and `max_parallel`\n55\t  - [x] Define `executeFn` callback: takes `(epicId, worktreePath)`, builds `EngineConfig` with `projectDir: worktreePath`, calls `executeWorkflow(config)` and returns the result\n56\t  - [x] Call `pool.startPool(epics, executeFn)` and await the `PoolResult`\n57\t  - [x] When `max_parallel === 1`, pool still runs (NFR10 — sequential through the pool, AC #9)\n58\t  - [x] When `epic_strategy === 'parallel'`, always use worktree isolation regardless of `execution.isolation` value (AC #12)\n59\t\n60\t- [x] Task 4: Implement lane event logging (AC: #10)\n61\t  - [x] Register `pool.onEvent(callback)` before starting the pool\n62\t  - [x] On `lane-started`: log `info('[LANE] Started epic {epicId} in lane {laneIndex}')`\n63\t  - [x] On `lane-completed`: log `ok('[LANE] Epic {epicId} completed in lane {laneIndex}')`\n64\t  - [x] On `lane-failed`: log `fail('[LANE] Epic {epicId} failed in lane {laneIndex}: {error}')`\n65\t  - [x] On `epic-queued`: log `info('[LANE] Epic {epicId} queued for execution')`\n66\t\n67\t- [x] Task 5: Implement result reporting for parallel execution (AC: #7)\n68\t  - [x] After `PoolResult` is returned, compute aggregate statistics: total epics, succeeded, failed, total stories processed, total duration\n69\t  - [x] If `poolResult.success`: log success message with aggregate stats, exit code 0\n70\t  - [x] If `!poolResult.success`: log failure message with per-epic breakdown, exit code 1\n71\t  - [x] For each failed epic: log the epic ID and error from `EpicResult`\n72\t\n73\t- [x] Task 6: Ensure worktree cleanup (AC: #11)\n74\t  - [x] Lane pool already handles cleanup on completion/failure (via `WorktreeManager.cleanupWorktree`)\n75\t  - [x] Verify this works by testing that after pool completion, no codeharness worktrees remain\n76\t  - [x] Add a safety net: after pool completes, call `worktreeManager.listWorktrees()` and warn if any remain\n77\t\n78\t- [x] Task 7: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#12)\n79\t  - [x] Test: parallel mode detected when `epic_strategy === 'parallel'`\n80\t  - [x] Test: sequential mode preserves existing single-engine behavior\n81\t  - [x] Test: LanePool created with correct `maxParallel` from execution config\n82\t  - [x] Test: epic descriptors built correctly from sprint state\n83\t  - [x] Test: executeFn sets `projectDir` to worktree path\n84\t  - [x] Test: pool result maps to correct exit code (0 for success, 1 for failure)\n85\t  - [x] Test: lane events are logged to console\n86\t  - [x] Test: `max_parallel: 1` with parallel strategy works correctly\n87\t  - [x] Test: parallel strategy forces worktree isolation regardless of `execution.isolation`\n88\t  - [x] Test: crash in one lane does not abort the run command\n89\t  - [x] Test: remaining worktrees are warned about after pool completion\n90\t\n91\t## Dev Notes\n92\t\n93\t### Architecture Constraints\n94\t\n95\t- **Architecture Decision 2** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): The engine maintains a fixed-size lane pool. Each lane is an async task that runs a workflow engine instance against a worktree directory. This story wires the lane pool into the run command.\n96\t- **Lane Isolation Pattern**: Each lane MUST set `cwd` to its worktree path for all agent dispatches. The `executeFn` callback achieves this by setting `EngineConfig.projectDir` to the worktree path.\n97\t- **Backward Compatibility** (NFR10): When `epic_strategy === 'sequential'`, the run command MUST use the existing single-engine execution path. No lane pool, no worktree manager. Zero behavior change.\n98\t\n99\t### Key Files to Modify\n100\t\n101\t| File | Why |\n102\t|------|-----|\n103\t| `src/commands/run.ts` | Main integration point — add parallel execution branch after workflow resolution |\n104\t\n105\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n106\t\n107\t| File | Why |\n108\t|------|-----|\n109\t| `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` | `LanePool` class, `EpicDescriptor`, `PoolResult`, `LaneEvent` interfaces — used directly in the run command. |\n110\t| `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` | `WorktreeManager` class — instantiated by the run command for parallel mode. |\n111\t| `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` | `executeWorkflow()`, `EngineConfig`, `EngineResult` — the engine is the `executeFn` callback target. |\n112\t| `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` | `ExecutionConfig` interface — has `max_parallel`, `epic_strategy`, `isolation`. |\n113\t| `src/modules/sprint/index.ts` | `getSprintState()`, `readSprintStatusFromState()` — for discovering pending epics and their stories. |\n114\t| `src/types/state.ts` | `SprintState`, `EpicState`, `StoryState` — for reading epic/story data. |\n115\t| `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` | `ResolvedWorkflow` — has `execution`, `storyFlow`, `epicFlow` fields. |\n116\t\n117\t### Implementation Patterns\n118\t\n119\t**Parallel execution branch in run command:**\n120\t```typescript\n121\t// After workflow resolution and agent resolution...\n122\tconst { execution } = parsedWorkflow;\n123\t\n124\tif (execution.epic_strategy === 'parallel') {\n125\t  // Parallel path: lane pool + worktrees\n126\t  const worktreeManager = new WorktreeManager();\n127\t  const pool = new LanePool(worktreeManager, execution.max_parallel);\n128\t\n129\t  // Register event listener for console output\n130\t  pool.onEvent((event) => { /* log lane events */ });\n131\t\n132\t  // Build epic descriptors from sprint state\n133\t  const epics = buildEpicDescriptors(state);\n134\t\n135\t  // Define executeFn: runs engine in worktree\n136\t  const executeFn: ExecuteEpicFn = async (epicId, worktreePath) => {\n137\t    const epicConfig: EngineConfig = {\n138\t      ...config,\n139\t      projectDir: worktreePath,\n140\t    };\n141\t    return executeWorkflow(epicConfig);\n142\t  };\n143\t\n144\t  const result = await pool.startPool(epics, executeFn);\n145\t  // Report results...\n146\t} else {\n147\t  // Sequential path: existing single-engine behavior (unchanged)\n148\t  const result = await executeWorkflow(config);\n149\t  // Existing reporting...\n150\t}\n151\t```\n152\t\n153\t**Epic descriptor construction from sprint state:**\n154\t```typescript\n155\tfunction buildEpicDescriptors(state: SprintState): EpicDescriptor[] {\n156\t  const epicMap = new Map<string, string[]>();\n157\t  for (const [storyKey, story] of Object.entries(state.stories)) {\n158\t    const epicId = extractEpicId(storyKey);\n159\t    if (!epicMap.has(epicId)) epicMap.set(epicId, []);\n160\t    epicMap.get(epicId)!.push(storyKey);\n161\t  }\n162\t\n163\t  return [...epicMap.entries()]\n164\t    .filter(([epicId]) => state.epics[`epic-${epicId}`]?.status !== 'done')\n165\t    .map(([epicId, stories]) => ({\n166\t      id: epicId,\n167\t      slug: `epic-${epicId}`,\n168\t      stories,\n169\t    }));\n170\t}\n171\t```\n172\t\n173\t**Testing strategy:** Mock `WorktreeManager`, `LanePool`, and `executeWorkflow` with `vi.mock()`. Verify the run command creates the pool with correct config, passes correct `executeFn`, and reports results correctly. Test both parallel and sequential paths. Use fake sprint state fixtures.\n174\t\n175\t### Previous Story (17-2) Intelligence\n176\t\n177\t- Story 17-2 completed the lane pool module. The `LanePool` class has `startPool(epics, executeFn) -> PoolResult` and `onEvent(callback)`. All types are exported.\n178\t- Story 17-1 completed the worktree manager. `WorktreeManager` has `createWorktree(epicId, slug) -> string` and `cleanupWorktree(epicId)`.\n179\t- Both modules are standalone — this story wires them into the run command.\n180\t- Current test count: ~4850+ tests across 178+ files. All passing.\n181\t- Module patterns: TypeScript in `src/`, ESM with `.js` import extensions, vitest test framework.\n182\t\n183\t### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n184\t\n185\t- **Merge operations** -- deferred to Epic 18. The run command does not merge worktrees. The lane pool creates and cleans up worktrees, but merging is a separate concern.\n186\t- **Epic completion detection** -- deferred to Story 19-1. The run command does not trigger epic_flow tasks.\n187\t- **TUI components** -- deferred to Epic 20. The run command logs lane events to console, not to multi-lane TUI.\n188\t- **State reconciliation across worktrees** -- deferred to Epic 18/19. Each worktree has its own local state; merging state is not in scope.\n189\t\n190\t### Edge Cases\n191\t\n192\t- **No pending epics**: All epics in sprint state are done. The run command should report \"no stories ready\" (existing behavior) or pass an empty array to the pool (which returns immediately with success).\n193\t- **Single epic with parallel strategy**: One epic, one lane. Pool runs it and completes. No worktree isolation benefit, but the path should work correctly.\n194\t- **All epics fail**: Pool returns `success: false`. Run command exits with code 1 and reports per-epic failures.\n195\t- **Workflow with no `execution` section**: Defaults to `epic_strategy: 'sequential'`, `max_parallel: 1`. Existing behavior preserved.\n196\t- **executeFn throws synchronously**: Should not happen (`executeWorkflow` is async), but the pool handles promise rejections.\n197\t- **WorktreeManager fails to create worktree for first epic**: Pool treats it as lane failure, continues with remaining epics.\n198\t- **`--resume` flag with parallel mode**: Resume semantics apply per-epic — each worktree's workflow state determines where to resume. This may need the engine to look for worktree-local state.\n199\t\n200\t### Project Structure Notes\n201\t\n202\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n203\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/` and `src/commands/__tests__/` directories\n204\t- ESM modules -- use `.js` extensions in imports\n205\t- Build: `npm run build`\n206\t- Test: `npm test`\n207\t\n208\t### References\n209\t\n210\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 17.3]\n211\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 2 -- Lane Pool & Scheduling]\n212\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Lane Isolation Pattern]\n213\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Modified Files -- run.ts]\n214\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#FR6, FR7, FR8, FR9, FR10]\n215\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#NFR6, NFR10]\n216\t"}]},"pare